1
00:00:16,690 --> 00:00:19,570
[band plays marching music]

2
00:00:21,950 --> 00:00:24,680
[woman in Spanish]
Citizens of Colombia,

3
00:00:24,700 --> 00:00:27,680
we present your new president,

4
00:00:27,800 --> 00:00:29,690
Pablo Escobar!

5
00:00:29,710 --> 00:00:31,840
[crowd cheering]

6
00:00:35,800 --> 00:00:39,430
[crowd chanting]
Pablo! Pablo! Pablo!

7
00:00:40,890 --> 00:00:42,010
[Pablo]
Thank you.

8
00:00:43,310 --> 00:00:44,930
How are you, sir?

9
00:00:45,690 --> 00:00:47,650
[crowd cheering]

10
00:00:51,770 --> 00:00:53,230
Thank you.

11
00:00:56,860 --> 00:00:58,160
Thank you.

12
00:01:03,080 --> 00:01:04,080
Much appreciated.

13
00:01:08,290 --> 00:01:09,710
Thank you.

14
00:01:10,670 --> 00:01:12,210
Please come in, Mr. President.

15
00:01:15,300 --> 00:01:16,650
[door closes]

16
00:01:16,670 --> 00:01:20,430
- [band continues in distance]
- [crowd continues chanting outside]

17
00:01:34,900 --> 00:01:36,150
Mmm.

18
00:01:37,450 --> 00:01:39,210
- All yours.
- Thank you.

19
00:01:39,240 --> 00:01:41,740
[marching drums playing]

20
00:01:45,160 --> 00:01:49,220
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

21
00:01:49,250 --> 00:01:52,670
- ♪ Happy birthday to you ♪
- What's this?

22
00:01:53,380 --> 00:01:57,020
♪ Happy birthday, dear Pablo ♪

23
00:01:57,050 --> 00:02:00,530
[singing continues over radio]
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

24
00:02:00,550 --> 00:02:02,030
[family cheers over radio]

25
00:02:02,050 --> 00:02:03,910
[Hermilda]
Bravo, Pablito.

26
00:02:03,930 --> 00:02:07,410
I love you, son.
Don't eat the whole cake.

27
00:02:07,430 --> 00:02:10,250
[Juan Pablo]
Don't forget to blow out the candles, Dad.

28
00:02:10,270 --> 00:02:14,690
[Manuela]
Happy birthday, Daddy!

29
00:02:15,610 --> 00:02:17,590
[Tata]
Pablo, we miss you so much.

30
00:02:17,610 --> 00:02:19,760
We wish we could be there with you.

31
00:02:19,780 --> 00:02:21,450
[Pablo]
I know, my love.

32
00:02:22,240 --> 00:02:25,490
Soon this will all be behind us.

33
00:02:26,700 --> 00:02:28,160
I promise.

34
00:02:35,130 --> 00:02:38,170
[Latin guitar theme music plays]

35
00:04:10,180 --> 00:04:12,740
[Steve] Look up "magical realism"
in the dictionary,

36
00:04:12,770 --> 00:04:15,450
and it'll describe a literary style

37
00:04:15,480 --> 00:04:17,620
incorporating fantastic
or mythical elements

38
00:04:17,650 --> 00:04:19,860
into otherwise realistic fiction.

39
00:04:20,650 --> 00:04:22,530
Colombia is where it began.

40
00:04:23,150 --> 00:04:25,960
And anyone who's spent real time here
knows why.

41
00:04:25,990 --> 00:04:29,260
It's a place where the bizarre
shakes hands with the inexplicable

42
00:04:29,280 --> 00:04:30,330
on a daily basis.

43
00:04:31,700 --> 00:04:35,020
But just like in the novels
of Gabriel García Márquez,

44
00:04:35,040 --> 00:04:39,170
the weird shit usually pops off
at certain critical moments.

45
00:04:40,500 --> 00:04:42,250
When the whole place is on edge.

46
00:04:44,380 --> 00:04:46,680
When everything's about to change.

47
00:04:48,930 --> 00:04:53,660
Of all the people who had
a vested interest in nailing Escobar,

48
00:04:53,680 --> 00:04:56,440
Javier Peña deserved to be there
when it went down.

49
00:04:57,560 --> 00:05:01,230
No American had given more or done more.

50
00:05:04,320 --> 00:05:05,990
[Steve] Well... [sighs]

51
00:05:06,950 --> 00:05:08,280
To, uh...

52
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:11,200
the Drug Enforcement Administration?

53
00:05:12,330 --> 00:05:14,390
I'll drink to that while I still can.

54
00:05:14,410 --> 00:05:16,120
You're a fucking lifer, Javi.

55
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:24,820
Well, it doesn't take a genius
to figure out which long-term DEA agent

56
00:05:24,840 --> 00:05:26,940
was linked to the Los Pepes death squad.

57
00:05:26,970 --> 00:05:28,990
Well, the Board of Professional Conduct

58
00:05:29,010 --> 00:05:31,400
has never been accused
of being geniuses, so...

59
00:05:31,430 --> 00:05:34,180
Yeah, and who reads
the Miami Herald anyway, right?

60
00:05:40,690 --> 00:05:42,020
Murphy, listen.

61
00:05:43,230 --> 00:05:44,570
I meant what I said.

62
00:05:46,490 --> 00:05:49,800
Anyone starts asking questions, just
tell them what they want to hear, okay?

63
00:05:49,820 --> 00:05:53,430
- It was always on me.
- Fuck you, Javi. [chuckles]

64
00:05:53,450 --> 00:05:55,620
And anybody who comes around asking.

65
00:06:01,290 --> 00:06:03,130
Well, you do me a favor. You...

66
00:06:06,210 --> 00:06:07,630
You get him.

67
00:06:09,840 --> 00:06:11,860
[woman over PA]
Attention passengers.

68
00:06:11,890 --> 00:06:18,290
We will now start boarding Flight 464
to Washington, D.C. at Gate Two.

69
00:06:18,310 --> 00:06:21,290
All right, well, I gotta...
I can't finish this. It's...

70
00:06:21,310 --> 00:06:22,350
I gotta go.

71
00:06:24,770 --> 00:06:26,070
[Steve sighs]

72
00:06:29,950 --> 00:06:31,200
[Javier]
Take care of yourself.

73
00:06:39,540 --> 00:06:41,730
[Steve]
All it took was the whiff of a scandal

74
00:06:41,750 --> 00:06:43,980
out of the mouth of an exiled drug queen

75
00:06:44,000 --> 00:06:47,090
and Peña was gone, like fucking magic.

76
00:06:47,760 --> 00:06:51,430
- [upbeat Latin music playing]
- [food sizzling]

77
00:07:23,580 --> 00:07:27,340
- [garage door closes]
- [dogs barking outside]

78
00:07:29,550 --> 00:07:30,920
Good morning, boss.

79
00:07:32,090 --> 00:07:33,630
I made some eggs.

80
00:07:34,550 --> 00:07:37,470
- There's leftover cake.
- Yes, sir.

81
00:07:38,100 --> 00:07:39,140
Thanks.

82
00:07:42,640 --> 00:07:44,810
I got everything we need, boss.

83
00:07:45,810 --> 00:07:48,210
You went to a different store, correct?

84
00:07:48,230 --> 00:07:50,730
Yes, sir.
I go to a different one every time.

85
00:07:53,650 --> 00:07:57,740
So, the shopkeeper's mom, she's a healer.

86
00:07:59,830 --> 00:08:01,580
I paid her a visit.

87
00:08:03,040 --> 00:08:06,580
I told you not to talk to anybody.

88
00:08:07,540 --> 00:08:09,000
Yeah, boss, but...

89
00:08:10,750 --> 00:08:16,050
only thing is, since I was a kid,
I've believed in these things.

90
00:08:17,510 --> 00:08:18,680
Look...

91
00:08:19,930 --> 00:08:23,270
I asked her for something to protect you.

92
00:08:24,600 --> 00:08:26,850
The sword of St. Michael the archangel...

93
00:08:27,400 --> 00:08:30,130
- the Virgin...
- ...and the Holy Child of Atocha.

94
00:08:30,150 --> 00:08:31,570
Mmm-hmm.

95
00:08:34,990 --> 00:08:39,240
You know my mother and I built a church?

96
00:08:40,580 --> 00:08:41,700
Yes, sir.

97
00:08:43,000 --> 00:08:44,930
In Barrio Pablo Escobar.

98
00:08:44,960 --> 00:08:46,540
That's where I grew up, boss.

99
00:08:48,460 --> 00:08:50,250
Happy birthday, sir.

100
00:08:51,250 --> 00:08:53,050
Thank you, Limón.

101
00:08:54,720 --> 00:08:56,090
Pardon me.

102
00:09:00,970 --> 00:09:04,490
[Pablo's family]
♪ Happy birthday to you ♪

103
00:09:04,520 --> 00:09:08,500
♪ Happy birthday, dear Pablo ♪

104
00:09:08,520 --> 00:09:10,400
♪ Happy birthday... ♪

105
00:09:11,440 --> 00:09:13,750
[in English]
This signal is coming from Medellín.

106
00:09:13,780 --> 00:09:16,070
[in Spanish]
Casablanca neighborhood, to be exact.

107
00:09:16,700 --> 00:09:19,130
- [in English] Pablo's come home.
- [Hugo Jr.] I think so.

108
00:09:19,160 --> 00:09:21,050
Hopefully he will
speak to them again tomorrow.

109
00:09:21,080 --> 00:09:23,660
[in Spanish]
If he does, we'll be listening.

110
00:09:27,710 --> 00:09:29,040
[sighs]

111
00:09:42,810 --> 00:09:45,270
This stays between us, understood?

112
00:09:47,140 --> 00:09:51,920
We will set up a temporary base
in Casablanca.

113
00:09:51,940 --> 00:09:56,130
We need to act as quickly as possible
as soon as Escobar appears, understood?

114
00:09:56,150 --> 00:09:58,030
- Yes, Colonel.
- Good work.

115
00:10:02,830 --> 00:10:04,490
Lieutenant Martinez?

116
00:10:06,450 --> 00:10:10,330
How long since we heard anything
from Escobar? A month? A month and a half?

117
00:10:10,830 --> 00:10:12,330
A month and a half, sir.

118
00:10:13,000 --> 00:10:16,300
And that whole time you've been
in the van listening to static?

119
00:10:17,590 --> 00:10:20,090
Yes. Waiting.

120
00:10:21,140 --> 00:10:25,220
Stubbornness seems to run in my family.
It's in our blood.

121
00:10:28,480 --> 00:10:29,640
Excuse me.

122
00:10:33,610 --> 00:10:35,790
[upbeat Latin music
plays softly on radio]

123
00:10:35,820 --> 00:10:37,030
Six.

124
00:10:47,200 --> 00:10:51,920
Can you imagine what would happen
if cocaine were legal?

125
00:10:54,460 --> 00:10:55,460
It's your turn.

126
00:10:56,550 --> 00:11:00,190
I think if coke was legal, boss,

127
00:11:00,220 --> 00:11:04,970
you would be the boss of the world
and the cops couldn't touch you.

128
00:11:15,690 --> 00:11:16,820
Yes, sir.

129
00:11:17,860 --> 00:11:21,590
We're sure that the call came from
the Casablanca neighborhood in Medellín.

130
00:11:21,610 --> 00:11:24,090
This is the best intel
we've received in months.

131
00:11:24,110 --> 00:11:27,910
Don't underestimate him.
We've made that mistake in the past.

132
00:11:28,700 --> 00:11:31,100
Gentlemen, I want to be loud and clear.

133
00:11:31,120 --> 00:11:33,670
If your men are able to find Escobar...

134
00:11:35,670 --> 00:11:37,250
I don't care about the consequences.

135
00:11:40,090 --> 00:11:41,090
I want him dead.

136
00:11:42,880 --> 00:11:44,720
Do you have a problem with that?

137
00:11:47,010 --> 00:11:52,830
With all due respect, Mr. President,
if he resists, that's how it will go.

138
00:11:52,850 --> 00:11:55,100
Otherwise, we're going to capture him.

139
00:11:56,560 --> 00:11:57,940
Keep me informed.

140
00:12:01,440 --> 00:12:02,780
[man]
Gentlemen.

141
00:12:15,790 --> 00:12:17,500
[sighs]

142
00:12:38,650 --> 00:12:39,820
Mrs. Escobar?

143
00:12:40,690 --> 00:12:42,790
The attorney general called this morning.

144
00:12:42,820 --> 00:12:45,530
He's decided to end
your protective custody.

145
00:12:46,490 --> 00:12:49,760
So we have to leave by the weekend.

146
00:12:49,780 --> 00:12:53,510
No. No, you can't do this to us.

147
00:12:53,540 --> 00:12:56,830
They were waiting for your husband
to turn himself in, and he never did.

148
00:13:02,880 --> 00:13:04,880
Ma'am? Ma'am.

149
00:13:05,590 --> 00:13:07,680
May I give you some advice?

150
00:13:11,430 --> 00:13:15,330
I think it's time for you to think
about you and your children's safety.

151
00:13:15,350 --> 00:13:16,890
Forget about him.

152
00:13:28,990 --> 00:13:32,160
[broken radio chatter, static]

153
00:13:38,290 --> 00:13:41,750
[Tata] The kids miss you.
Should I wake up Juan Pablo?

154
00:13:43,630 --> 00:13:47,090
[Pablo] Probably not a good idea
right now, my love.

155
00:13:48,430 --> 00:13:51,350
[Tata]
So... do you feel a year older or what?

156
00:13:53,350 --> 00:13:55,640
More like four or five.

157
00:13:56,310 --> 00:13:58,310
We've missed you very much, Pablo.

158
00:13:58,940 --> 00:14:00,690
The days feel longer.

159
00:14:03,610 --> 00:14:05,150
For me too.

160
00:14:07,360 --> 00:14:09,760
I still don't understand
why you're in Medellín.

161
00:14:09,780 --> 00:14:11,950
That place is too dangerous, my love.

162
00:14:15,830 --> 00:14:19,500
That's exactly why.
No one would think I'd be here.

163
00:14:21,960 --> 00:14:22,960
Pablo...

164
00:14:23,920 --> 00:14:27,630
I think the time has come.
We don't have a choice.

165
00:14:29,590 --> 00:14:32,700
Turning yourself in
isn't the end of the world, my love.

166
00:14:32,720 --> 00:14:34,010
You can survive prison.

167
00:14:37,220 --> 00:14:40,290
We both know that won't happen.

168
00:14:40,310 --> 00:14:42,600
[Hugo Jr.]
Stop, stop, stop, stop! Shh!

169
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:45,830
- [Tata] Listen to me, Pablo.
- They're talking.

170
00:14:45,860 --> 00:14:48,840
- You will always be Pablo Escobar.
- Boss.

171
00:14:48,860 --> 00:14:52,170
You will always be that man
that's admired and followed.

172
00:14:52,200 --> 00:14:53,740
My man.

173
00:14:54,620 --> 00:14:57,300
My love, there's a lot of journalists
who want to speak with you.

174
00:14:57,330 --> 00:14:59,160
The people love you and follow you.

175
00:14:59,830 --> 00:15:02,270
[Pablo]
Tata, Limón wants me off.

176
00:15:02,290 --> 00:15:05,460
It's Escobar. Let's go west!
Fix the position, Morales.

177
00:15:07,210 --> 00:15:09,550
My love, look at Nelson Mandela.

178
00:15:11,170 --> 00:15:14,320
They put the man in jail,
but the people still believed in him.

179
00:15:14,340 --> 00:15:16,320
They gave him the Nobel Prize.

180
00:15:16,350 --> 00:15:21,330
They say he may even become president.
President, Pablo.

181
00:15:21,350 --> 00:15:23,330
Of the same country that imprisoned him.

182
00:15:23,350 --> 00:15:25,420
[Pablo] I need to hang up.
We'll talk about this later.

183
00:15:25,440 --> 00:15:27,170
[Hugo Jr.]
Alvaro, stop. Stop for a second.

184
00:15:27,190 --> 00:15:30,040
[Tata] All right, Pablo.
But think about what I'm saying.

185
00:15:30,070 --> 00:15:32,000
It's very important.

186
00:15:32,030 --> 00:15:35,070
It's our only way out really.

187
00:15:35,820 --> 00:15:37,740
Alvaro, let's go slowly.

188
00:15:38,410 --> 00:15:40,680
Colonel!
Colonel, this is Lieutenant Martinez.

189
00:15:40,700 --> 00:15:43,680
Think about turning yourself in, my love.
Think of your family.

190
00:15:43,710 --> 00:15:45,080
I'll think about it.

191
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:47,290
All right?

192
00:15:50,090 --> 00:15:51,760
I love you very much.

193
00:16:24,000 --> 00:16:25,250
Where are you going?

194
00:16:25,830 --> 00:16:27,190
To Medellín.

195
00:16:27,210 --> 00:16:31,760
What? No, no, no, Hermilda.
You can't leave.

196
00:16:32,710 --> 00:16:34,630
My son needs me.

197
00:16:35,880 --> 00:16:37,010
How so?

198
00:16:37,720 --> 00:16:39,100
What you want...

199
00:16:40,720 --> 00:16:43,980
for him to turn himself in
to those monsters...

200
00:16:44,640 --> 00:16:45,870
I don't want them to kill him.

201
00:16:45,890 --> 00:16:48,120
They're going to kill him either way,
and you know that.

202
00:16:48,150 --> 00:16:49,790
They won't if he turns himself in.

203
00:16:49,820 --> 00:16:52,750
- It's a trap! Tata, my God!
- Lower your voice.

204
00:16:52,780 --> 00:16:54,670
No! No, ma'am.

205
00:16:54,690 --> 00:17:01,180
I will not stay quiet when...
when I see you... betraying my son!

206
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:05,080
I have never betrayed Pablo.
Let's make that very clear.

207
00:17:05,750 --> 00:17:08,980
We're locked in this hotel
as if it were a jail.

208
00:17:09,000 --> 00:17:11,040
We can't even leave the country.

209
00:17:12,550 --> 00:17:17,050
And the only shot I have at
getting my children out of this alive...

210
00:17:18,180 --> 00:17:20,050
is for Pablo to turn himself in.

211
00:17:27,060 --> 00:17:28,440
My son...

212
00:17:29,810 --> 00:17:32,020
needs his mother.

213
00:17:39,610 --> 00:17:40,870
Hermilda.

214
00:17:49,960 --> 00:17:53,250
Please be very careful. Please.

215
00:17:54,250 --> 00:17:56,010
Tell the children...

216
00:17:58,930 --> 00:18:00,430
[whispers] I'll tell them.

217
00:18:18,400 --> 00:18:21,360
[in Spanish] We have intel
that Escobar is in this building.

218
00:18:22,120 --> 00:18:25,950
Listen up. I want you to do
what you can to get him alive.

219
00:18:26,660 --> 00:18:29,640
Escobar must be brought to justice
before the people of Colombia

220
00:18:29,660 --> 00:18:33,460
and answer for the atrocious crimes
he has committed against this nation.

221
00:18:34,170 --> 00:18:37,710
Now, if he resists...

222
00:18:38,420 --> 00:18:41,550
if a single one of our men
is in harm's way...

223
00:18:42,340 --> 00:18:44,280
I want you to take his life. Understood?

224
00:18:44,300 --> 00:18:46,120
- [all] Yes, Colonel!
- Let's go.

225
00:18:46,140 --> 00:18:47,970
[engines revving]

226
00:19:34,770 --> 00:19:36,520
[Limón]
Everything all right, boss?

227
00:19:58,040 --> 00:19:59,800
Tata wants me to surrender.

228
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:07,140
[sighs]
She said I can be like Nelson Mandela.

229
00:20:08,260 --> 00:20:09,430
Nelson Mandela?

230
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:15,310
Who's that, boss?

231
00:21:06,400 --> 00:21:08,110
Did you buy more rolling papers?

232
00:21:08,740 --> 00:21:10,280
Sorry, no, boss.

233
00:21:18,830 --> 00:21:20,130
[knocking at door]

234
00:21:22,000 --> 00:21:23,170
[gasps]

235
00:21:23,840 --> 00:21:26,380
[fork clatters]

236
00:21:44,530 --> 00:21:48,070
I can't think with that
fucking smell of Chinese food in here.

237
00:22:09,430 --> 00:22:10,930
[man over radio]
He's not here.

238
00:22:16,140 --> 00:22:19,560
Come inside.
You can't risk being seen, sir.

239
00:22:22,480 --> 00:22:24,610
This is my city, Limón.

240
00:22:28,570 --> 00:22:30,320
These are my people.

241
00:22:33,950 --> 00:22:37,200
Medellín will never betray me.

242
00:22:41,580 --> 00:22:43,960
- [low chatter]
- Colonel.

243
00:22:44,500 --> 00:22:46,560
- We fucked up again, sir.
- He's not here.

244
00:22:46,590 --> 00:22:49,480
- Looks like your little machine is broken.
- [men chuckle]

245
00:22:49,510 --> 00:22:51,550
Go and fiddle with the little knob. Go on.

246
00:22:52,930 --> 00:22:54,430
Excuse me, Colonel.

247
00:22:58,680 --> 00:23:02,770
[man] Listen up! Take down
the staging area and head back to Holguín.

248
00:23:13,660 --> 00:23:16,990
[Hugo Jr.] Son of a bitch wasn't talking
from this building, but he was close.

249
00:23:17,700 --> 00:23:20,710
- [kids chattering]
- [water splashes]

250
00:23:21,790 --> 00:23:24,920
- A ghost.
- What's that?

251
00:23:25,670 --> 00:23:29,520
That's what you call a signal that's been
reflected and appears somewhere else.

252
00:23:29,550 --> 00:23:32,630
That's what happened with Escobar's
signal. It bounced off the water.

