00:48:17,700 --> 00:48:22,250
He told me that you were a decent man.
That you would understand the situation.

508
00:48:24,290 --> 00:48:25,880
That you would forgive us.

509
00:48:27,340 --> 00:48:29,880
And that you might help us
get out of the country.

510
00:48:32,630 --> 00:48:35,610
How much do you have left, Mrs. Escobar?

511
00:48:35,640 --> 00:48:38,220
In property? In cash?

512
00:48:43,020 --> 00:48:44,270
I can find out.

513
00:48:47,900 --> 00:48:49,440
That's good.

514
00:48:50,230 --> 00:48:52,150
Because I want all of it.

515
00:49:30,610 --> 00:49:32,690
[Javier in English]
Sir, do I need a lawyer?

516
00:49:35,240 --> 00:49:37,070
You're the review board, right?

517
00:49:38,410 --> 00:49:41,870
Professional conduct or some bullshit?

518
00:49:44,450 --> 00:49:45,910
We're not the review board.

519
00:49:49,670 --> 00:49:50,840
So who are you?

520
00:49:53,550 --> 00:49:55,050
We're from Operations.

521
00:49:59,840 --> 00:50:01,410
What do you want from me?

522
00:50:01,430 --> 00:50:04,830
- [laughter, chatter]
- [in Spanish] All right, gentlemen!

523
00:50:04,850 --> 00:50:06,490
Gentlemen!

524
00:50:06,520 --> 00:50:12,630
In the history of every business,
there are decisive moments.

525
00:50:12,650 --> 00:50:14,590
In 1992, do you know how much cocaine

526
00:50:14,610 --> 00:50:16,820
we estimated came into the US
from Colombia?

527
00:50:18,280 --> 00:50:20,550
311 metric tons.

528
00:50:20,570 --> 00:50:25,850
The first sale. The first million.
The first billion.

529
00:50:25,870 --> 00:50:29,850
And when your rival no longer exists.

530
00:50:29,870 --> 00:50:31,290
[laughter]

531
00:50:32,000 --> 00:50:37,900
And in 1993, during the hunt for Escobar,
372 metric tons.

532
00:50:37,920 --> 00:50:40,440
Now that piece of shit is on his last leg.

533
00:50:40,470 --> 00:50:42,530
Every one of his labs has been shut down.

534
00:50:42,550 --> 00:50:44,950
And cocaine production goes up.

535
00:50:44,970 --> 00:50:48,120
The important thing in these moments
isn't how one reacts,

536
00:50:48,140 --> 00:50:50,540
but how well one has prepared for them.

537
00:50:50,560 --> 00:50:54,900
Gentlemen, I have to tell you
that we are ready.

538
00:50:55,650 --> 00:50:57,650
Can you imagine what happens next year?

539
00:50:58,400 --> 00:51:02,840
[Gilberto] And we won't be needing
kidnappings and bombs to succeed.

540
00:51:02,870 --> 00:51:06,220
We will do it covertly.

541
00:51:06,240 --> 00:51:09,100
And when they turn around
to see what happened,

542
00:51:09,120 --> 00:51:10,520
we'll no longer be there.

543
00:51:10,540 --> 00:51:12,350
- No, sir!
- [laughter]

544
00:51:12,380 --> 00:51:14,710
- Cheers!
- [all] Cheers!

545
00:51:15,840 --> 00:51:18,420
Now the king is dead. Long live the kings.

546
00:51:23,510 --> 00:51:27,520
Agent Peña, how much do you know
about the Cali cartel?

547
00:51:32,150 --> 00:51:34,520
[pop song plays]

